---
import Feature from '../../layouts/Feature.astro';
---

<Feature
  title="IMAGES"
  subtitle="Display images directly in your terminal. Photos, diagrams, emoji, even animated GIFs."
>
  <h2>Display Images Inline</h2>
  <p>ori-term can display images directly alongside your text. View photos, charts, diagrams, and screenshots without leaving the terminal. Images are GPU-accelerated, so they display smoothly without slowing down text rendering.</p>

  <h2>How to Display Images</h2>
  <p>Use any of these tools to display images in ori-term:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>kitten icat image.png</code> -- Recommended, most capable</li>
    <li><code>img2sixel image.png</code> -- Widely supported format</li>
    <li><code>imgcat image.png</code> -- iTerm2-compatible</li>
  </ul>
  <p>ori-term supports the three major terminal image formats, so most image-display tools work out of the box.</p>

  <h2>Animated GIFs</h2>
  <p>Animated GIFs play frame-by-frame at their intended timing. Watch animations right in your terminal.</p>

  <h2>Memory Limits</h2>
  <p>ori-term automatically manages image memory. A configurable limit (320 MB CPU-side, 512 MB GPU-side by default) ensures that long-running sessions with many images do not consume unbounded memory. Older images are evicted as needed to make room for new ones.</p>
</Feature>
